+## `duh.ports`
+
+The ports package exposes six protocols, re-exported from
+`duh.ports.__init__`:
+
+```python
+from duh.ports import (
+    ApprovalGate, ContextManager, MemoryHeader, MemoryStore,
+    ModelProvider, SessionStore, ToolExecutor,
+)
+```
+
+All of them are `typing.Protocol` subclasses, decorated with
+`@runtime_checkable`, so you can use `isinstance(obj, ModelProvider)`
+for duck-typed dispatch.
+
+### `duh.ports.approver.ApprovalGate`
+
+Checked before every tool execution by the query loop.
+
+```python
+class ApprovalGate(Protocol):
+    async def check(
+        self,
+        tool_name: str,
+        input: dict[str, Any],
+    ) -> dict[str, Any]: ...
+```
+
+- **Returns**: `{"allowed": True}` or `{"allowed": False, "reason": "…"}`.
+- **Raises**: implementations should not raise; a denial is signalled
+  through the return value.
+
+**Example**
+
+```python
+class YesAll:
+    async def check(self, tool_name, input):
+        return {"allowed": True}
+```
+
+### `duh.ports.context.ContextManager`
+
+Compacts messages when the token budget is exceeded.
+
+```python
+class ContextManager(Protocol):
+    async def compact(
+        self, messages: list[Any], token_limit: int,
+    ) -> list[Any]: ...
+
+    def estimate_tokens(self, messages: list[Any]) -> int: ...
+```
+
+- `compact` returns a **new** list — it must not mutate `messages`.
+
+### `duh.ports.executor.ToolExecutor`
+
+Finds, validates, and runs a tool by name.
+
+```python
+class ToolExecutor(Protocol):
+    async def run(
+        self,
+        tool_name: str,
+        input: dict[str, Any],
+        *,
+        tool_use_id: str = "",
+        context: Any = None,
+    ) -> str | dict[str, Any]: ...
+```
+
+- Returns the tool's output as a string or dict.
+- Raises on tool-not-found or execution errors.
+
+### `duh.ports.memory.MemoryHeader`
+
+Immutable metadata for a single memory topic file.
+
+```python
+@dataclass(frozen=True)
+class MemoryHeader:
+    filename: str
+    name: str
+    description: str
+    type: str  # "user" | "feedback" | "project" | "reference"
+```
+
+### `duh.ports.memory.MemoryStore`
+
+Persists per-project memory. File-based by convention; stored under
+`~/.config/duh/projects/<sanitized-cwd>/memory/`.
+
+```python
+class MemoryStore(Protocol):
+    def get_memory_dir(self) -> Path: ...
+    def read_index(self) -> str: ...
+    def write_index(self, content: str) -> None: ...
+    def read_file(self, name: str) -> str: ...
+    def write_file(self, name: str, content: str) -> None: ...
+    def list_files(self) -> list[MemoryHeader]: ...
+    def delete_file(self, name: str) -> None: ...
+```
+
+`write_index` truncates to the last 200 lines. `read_*` return empty
+string when the target is missing — they never raise.
+
+### `duh.ports.provider.ModelProvider`
+
+The LLM-facing port. Every provider (Anthropic, OpenAI, Ollama, Gemini,
+Groq, stub) implements this.
+
+```python
+class ModelProvider(Protocol):
+    async def stream(
+        self,
+        *,
+        messages: list[Any],
+        system_prompt: str | list[str] = "",
+        model: str = "",
+        tools: list[Any] | None = None,
+        thinking: dict[str, Any] | None = None,
+        max_tokens: int | None = None,
+        **kwargs: Any,
+    ) -> AsyncGenerator[dict[str, Any], None]: ...
+```
+
+Must yield events in D.U.H.'s uniform event schema:
+
+- `{"type": "text_delta", "text": "…"}`
+- `{"type": "thinking_delta", "text": "…"}`
+- `{"type": "tool_use", "id": "…", "name": "…", "input": {…}}`
+- `{"type": "assistant", "message": Message}` — the completed turn
+- `{"type": "error", "error": "…"}`
+
+### `duh.ports.renderer.Renderer`
+
+Consumes engine events, produces terminal output. Three built-in tiers:
+`Bare`, `Rich`, and full TUI.
+
+```python
+class Renderer(Protocol):
+    def render_text_delta(self, text: str) -> None: ...
+    def render_tool_use(self, name: str, input: dict[str, Any]) -> None: ...
+    def render_tool_result(self, output: str, is_error: bool) -> None: ...
+    def render_thinking(self, text: str) -> None: ...
+    def render_error(self, error: str) -> None: ...
+    def render_permission_request(
+        self, tool_name: str, input: dict[str, Any]
+    ) -> None: ...
+    def finish(self) -> None: ...
+    def handle(self, event: dict[str, Any]) -> None: ...
+```
+
+`handle(event)` is the main dispatcher — it routes an event to the
+appropriate `render_*` method based on `event["type"]`.
+
+### `duh.ports.store.SessionStore`
+
+Persists entire sessions (messages).
+
+```python
+class SessionStore(Protocol):
+    async def save(self, session_id: str, messages: list[Any]) -> None: ...
+    async def load(self, session_id: str) -> list[Any] | None: ...
+    async def list_sessions(self) -> list[dict[str, Any]]: ...
+    async def delete(self, session_id: str) -> bool: ...
+```
+
+`load` returns `None` when not found. `delete` returns `True` if the
+session existed.
