+
+### `ContextGate`
+
+`duh.kernel.context_gate`.
+
+```python
+class ContextGate:
+    BLOCK_THRESHOLD = 0.95
+
+    def __init__(self, context_limit: int): ...
+    def check(self, token_estimate: int) -> tuple[bool, str]: ...
+```
+
+Returns `(True, "")` when the estimate is under 95 % of the context
+window, else `(False, reason)` with a human-readable explanation.
+The engine uses this gate *after* auto-compaction and before any API
+call.
+
+---
+
+### `ConfirmationMinter`
+
+`duh.kernel.confirmation`. Single-use HMAC-bound tokens for dangerous
+tool calls.
+
+```python
+class ConfirmationMinter:
+    def __init__(self, session_key: bytes): ...
+    def mint(self, session_id: str, tool: str, input_obj: dict) -> str
+    def validate(
+        self, token: str, session_id: str, tool: str, input_obj: dict
+    ) -> bool
+```
+
+Tokens embed `session_id | tool_name | sha256(input) | timestamp`
+and an HMAC signature. `validate` returns `False` for any token older
+than 300 s, replayed (already seen), or bound to a different
+session/tool/input.
+
+---
+
+### `UntrustedStr`
+
+`duh.kernel.untrusted`. A `str` subclass that carries a `TaintSource`
+tag through string operations.
+
+```python
+class TaintSource(str, Enum):
+    USER_INPUT = "user_input"      # untainted
+    MODEL_OUTPUT = "model_output"  # tainted
+    TOOL_OUTPUT = "tool_output"    # tainted
+    FILE_CONTENT = "file_content"  # tainted
+    MCP_OUTPUT = "mcp_output"      # tainted
+    NETWORK = "network"            # tainted
+    SYSTEM = "system"              # untainted
+
+UNTAINTED_SOURCES: frozenset[TaintSource]  # {USER_INPUT, SYSTEM}
+
+class UntrustedStr(str):
+    def __new__(
+        cls,
+        value: object = "",
+        source: TaintSource = TaintSource.MODEL_OUTPUT,
+    ) -> "UntrustedStr": ...
+
+    source: TaintSource             # property
+    def is_tainted(self) -> bool
+```
+
+Every str method that returns a `str` is overridden to return an
+`UntrustedStr` carrying the same or merged source: `__add__`,
+`__mod__`, `__mul__`, `format`, `format_map`, `join`, `replace`,
+`strip`, `lstrip`, `rstrip`, `split`, `rsplit`, `splitlines`, `lower`,
+`upper`, `title`, `casefold`, `capitalize`, `swapcase`, `expandtabs`,
+`center`, `ljust`, `rjust`, `zfill`, `translate`, `removeprefix`,
+`removesuffix`, `__getitem__`, and `__format__`.
+
+Helpers:
+
+```python
+def merge_source(a: Any, b: Any) -> TaintSource
+def assert_no_tag_loss(value: object, op: str) -> None
+
+class TaintLossError(RuntimeError): ...
+```
+
+Environment variables: `DUH_TAINT_DEBUG=1` logs preserved ops;
+`DUH_TAINT_STRICT=1` raises `TaintLossError` on silent drops.
+
