+
+### Attachments
+
+`duh.kernel.attachments`.
+
+```python
+MAX_ATTACHMENT_SIZE = 20 * 1024 * 1024  # 20 MB
+
+@dataclass
+class Attachment:
+    name: str
+    content_type: str
+    data: bytes
+    metadata: dict[str, Any]
+
+    size: int        # len(self.data)
+    is_image: bool
+    text: str | None
+    base64: str
+
+class AttachmentManager:
+    def read_file(self, path: str) -> Attachment
+    def detect_content_type(self, filename: str, data: bytes) -> str
+    def to_image_block(self, attachment: Attachment) -> ImageBlock
+    def extract_text(self, attachment: Attachment) -> str
+```
+
+`read_file` raises `FileNotFoundError` on a missing path and
+`ValueError` when the file exceeds `MAX_ATTACHMENT_SIZE`.
+`to_image_block` raises `ValueError` when the attachment isn't an
+image.
+
