+
+### Memory integration
+
+`duh.kernel.memory`.
+
+```python
+MEMORY_TYPES: dict[str, str]   # "user", "feedback", "project", "reference"
+
+FRONTMATTER_TEMPLATE: str
+
+def make_frontmatter(*, name: str, description: str, type: str) -> str
+def build_memory_prompt(store: MemoryStore) -> str
+```
+
+`build_memory_prompt` reads `MEMORY.md` and up to the 20 most recent
+facts via `store.list_facts()` (when available) and returns a
+`<memory>` tag suitable for system prompt injection. Returns `""`
+when neither exists.
+
+### Memory decay
+
+`duh.kernel.memory_decay`.
+
+```python
+def score_facts(
+    facts: list[dict[str, Any]],
+    *,
+    now: datetime | None = None,
+) -> list[tuple[dict[str, Any], float]]
+
+def gc_memories(
+    store: Any,
+    *,
+    max_facts: int = 200,
+    min_score: float = 0.1,
+    now: datetime | None = None,
+) -> int
+```
+
+`score_facts` returns `(fact, score)` tuples sorted score-descending.
+Score = `0.5 * recency + 0.2 * creation + 0.3 * access_count`. Each
+term is normalised to [0, 1]. `gc_memories` removes facts below
+`min_score`, then trims to `max_facts` from the tail; returns the
+removal count.
+
