+# D.U.H. Documentation
+
+D.U.H. — Duh is a Universal Harness — is a provider-agnostic AI coding
+agent with a deliberately small, stdlib-only kernel and a library of
+adapters for Anthropic, OpenAI, Gemini, Groq, Ollama, and (optionally)
+LiteLLM. This documentation set covers commit `645d91a` (v0.8.0).
+
+The three documents below form a coherent set: the architecture
+describes the shape of the system, the tutorial walks you through
+using it end-to-end, and the API reference is the machine-checkable
+contract that both other documents point at.
+
+## [ARCHITECTURE.md](ARCHITECTURE.md)
+
+Top-level tour of the codebase. Covers the package layout with a
+component diagram, the step-by-step data flow of a single user
+request from CLI parse through the `Engine.run` orchestration into
+the `query()` loop and out through a `Renderer`, the four extension
+points (provider adapters, tools, slash commands, skills, plus
+hooks), the four-layer security model (`UntrustedStr` taint,
+`ConfirmationMinter` tokens, OS sandboxes, the lethal-trifecta
+capability check), the asyncio-based concurrency model with
+`QueryGuard` and `JobQueue`, and an honest list of the tradeoffs
+and non-goals the project has committed to.
+
+## [TUTORIAL.md](TUTORIAL.md)
+
+"From zero to your first custom tool." Install D.U.H., run a
+stub-mode session with no credentials, drive `Engine.run` from
+Python, write a `TodayTool` that implements the `Tool` protocol
+(schema, `call`, `check_permissions`), validate its schema, register
